HEADWORD: Racahout
<hw>Ra`ca`hout"</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧`k⟦adot⟧`⟦oomac⟧")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>racahout</ets>, probably fr. Ar.
<ets>r⟦amac⟧qaut</ets>.]</ety> <def>A preparation from acorns used by
the Arabs as a substitute for chocolate, and also as a beverage for
invalids.</def>⟦br⟧
